column2: QUESTION
COMPILATION
The code compiled from the first try
The code did no compile initially, but was fixed with minor corrections / changes
MAIN ACTIVITY
Does the app contain all three components: MainActivity, MediaPlayerService and AccelerationService?
Does the MainActivity layout contain the commands: play, pause, stop, exit, gesturesOn and gesturesOff?
Are the following commands executed properly through the MainActivity: play, pause and stop?
Are the following commands executed properly through the MainActivity: gesturesOn and gesturesOff?
column5: G-OFF doesn’t seem to be working. After pressing it, music still keeps playing on the movement

column2: Is the following command executed properly through the MainActivity: exit?
column5: on exit it gives "miniapp keeps stopping" and "java.lang.RuntimeException: Unable to start service si.uni_lj.fri.pbd.miniapp2.MediaPlayerService@e454e04 with null: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Parameter specified as non-null is null: method kotlin.jvm.internal.Intrinsics.checkParameterIsNotNull, parameter intent"

column2: Does the MainActivity layout displays correct track title, duration information and progress bar (e.g., receives updates every second)?
Is the progress bar implemented using coroutines?
Does to MainActivity use a Binder to connect to the MediaPlayerService?
MEDIA_PLAYER_SERVICE
Is the MediaPlayerService implemented as a foreground service?
Does the MediaPlayerService notification allow the commands: play, pause, stop and exit? (it is OK if there are only three visible at a time )
Are the following commands executed properly through MediaPlayerService notification: play, pause and stop?
Does the MediaPlayerService notification displays correct track title and duration information (e.g., receives updates every second)?
Is the track title and duration information equal both in the MainActivity and in the foreground notification after closing and re-opening the MainActivity?
ACCELERATION_SERVICE
Is the AccelerationService implemented as a Service?
Does the AccelerationService read data from the phone's Accelerometer sensor?
Does the AccelerationService contain gesture-recognition algorithm for recognizing IDLE vs. HORIZONTAL vs. VERTICAL ? (mark 1, even if it does not function completely properly)
Using the emulator, with the app runing and MainActivity active, perform several random gestures (HORIZONTAL or VERTICAL) in a row with a few seconds pause in between.
Does the gesture-recognition algorithm correctly recognize at least 50% (e.g.,  2 out of 4) of the HORIZONTAL gestures?
Does the gesture-recognition algorithm correctly recognize at least 50% (e.g., 2 out of 4) of the VERTICAL gestures?
Does the MainActivity layout displays correct track title and the duration after each recognized gesture?
GENERAL
Is the code sufficiently well commented in English?
Is the following statement true (it does not include the Bonus task): "The app did not crash at any time during testing"
BONUS TASK
Does the app contain code for the Bonus task (e.g., significant amount of code not required for the main part of the application)
Does the app allow to train a machine learning model for user-defined gesture recognition (mark 1, even if it does not function completely properly)
Does the app include the pre-trained model and a "gestures.txt" file describing the two gestures the model was trained on?
column5: No such file in the root folder

column2: Did the pre-trained app successfully recognize user's gestures?
Is the following statement true: "The app did not crash while I was testing the Bonus task"
Although there was some issues but it's obvious that a lot of work was dedicated for this app
